<paragraph blockId="13.[213,1169,168,638]" pageId="13" pageNumber="2935">
<emphasis box="[213,350,168,192]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="2935">Morphology</emphasis>
. Stemmaticum with irregular aciculate sculpture (
<figureCitation box="[915,1032,168,192]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="12.[146,213,1652,1674]" captionTargetBox="[160,1104,234,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-1@12.[146,1104,234,1616]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 3. Encarsia magnalata Shih, Ko and Polaszek, sp. nov. Female: (A) posterior head; (B) antenna; (C) mesosoma; (D) mid-leg; (E) ovipositor; (F) fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224455/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="2935">Figure 3A</figureCitation>
); frons with parallel aciculate sculpture. Antennal formula 1-1-4-2, but could be interpreted as 1- 1-3-3 (
<figureCitation box="[286,400,232,256]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="12.[146,213,1652,1674]" captionTargetBox="[160,1104,234,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-1@12.[146,1104,234,1616]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 3. Encarsia magnalata Shih, Ko and Polaszek, sp. nov. Female: (A) posterior head; (B) antenna; (C) mesosoma; (D) mid-leg; (E) ovipositor; (F) fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224455/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="2935">Figure 3B</figureCitation>
). Pedicel clearly longer and larger than F1. F1 1.2 times as long as its maximum width, clearly much shorter than F2 and F3, which are approximately equal in length. Flagellum with the following numbers of longitudinal sensilla: F1: 0, F2: 3, F3: 2–3, F4: 3, F5: 4, F6: 3. Mid-lobe of mesoscutum with 10 setae (
<figureCitation box="[220,336,359,383]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="12.[146,213,1652,1674]" captionTargetBox="[160,1104,234,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-1@12.[146,1104,234,1616]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 3. Encarsia magnalata Shih, Ko and Polaszek, sp. nov. Female: (A) posterior head; (B) antenna; (C) mesosoma; (D) mid-leg; (E) ovipositor; (F) fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224455/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="2935">Figure 3C</figureCitation>
). Side lobes with three setae. Scutellar sensilla distantly placed. Distance between anterior pair of scutellar setae very slightly less than that between posterior pair. Fore wing (
<figureCitation box="[407,519,423,447]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="12.[146,213,1652,1674]" captionTargetBox="[160,1104,234,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-1@12.[146,1104,234,1616]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 3. Encarsia magnalata Shih, Ko and Polaszek, sp. nov. Female: (A) posterior head; (B) antenna; (C) mesosoma; (D) mid-leg; (E) ovipositor; (F) fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5224455/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="2935">Figure 3F</figureCitation>
) 2.4 times as long as width of disc. Marginal fringe 0.16 times as long as width of disc. Submarginal vein with two setae, marginal vein anteriorly with seven to nine setae. Basal cell with two setae. Tarsal formula 5-5-5. Apical spur of mid-tibia long, almost as long as corresponding basitarsus. Tergites laterally with the following numbers of setae: T1: 0, T2: 2–4, T3: 2–3, T4: 2, T5: 3, T6: 2, T7: 4. Ovipositor longer than combined length of mid tibia and tarsus. Third valvula 0.64 times as long as second valvifer.
</paragraph>
